bib_record.title: Neutron resonance spectroscopy on 113Cd to En=15keV

free_txt: Corrected for background and dead-time losses.
Largest chemical contaminent was lead at 0.004%.
Data received by electronic mail, C.Frankle, 1996/9/26.
NE912 6Li loaded glass scintillator, viewed by
Neutron beam monitored by 235U fission chamber.
Pair of 1-l C6D6 liquid scintillation detectors.
Neutron beam monitored by 6Li glass detector.
Transmission on 113Cd and natural Cd and capture
data on 113Cd were analyzed with SAMMY using Reich-
Moore multilevel analysis. Data presented are weighted
average of parameters from both analyses.
For transmission data, assumed capture width of 100meV
for s-wave resonances and 160 meV for p-wave
*** By authors *** Parameters should be considered a
revision of the previous parameters from LAMPF
measurements (see data set 13145), Frankle, et al.,
Phys.Rev.C, 45, 2143 (1992), where they do not agree.
No information on source of uncertainties.
